# Adventure POS — Odoo rules

Derived from `docs/agent-rules.md`. Custom Odoo system: retail POS, inventory, customers, purchasing, reporting.

## Architecture

- All business logic MUST live in Odoo modules under `/addons/`.
- Do NOT modify Odoo core, place logic outside modules, or duplicate logic across modules.

## Module scope

Initial modules: `adventure_base`, `adventure_pos`, `adventure_inventory`, `adventure_customers`, `adventure_purchase`, `adventure_reports`. Use consistent `adventure_*` prefixes.

## Safe extension

- Prefer model inheritance (`_inherit`) and extension patterns over overrides.
- Preserve upgrade compatibility.
- Avoid monkey patching, deleting core behavior, and fragile XPath in XML.

## Configuration as code

- When agreed Odoo configuration must exist in every environment (or every new dev DB), encode it in git: module `data/` (XML/CSV), manifest hooks, or documented scripts—not UI-only on one machine.
- Do not treat UI-only setup as complete without a repeatable artifact. See `docs/agent-rules.md` (Configuration as code).

## Coding standards

- Python: Odoo conventions, small readable methods.
- XML: clean structure, minimal XPath complexity; comment non-obvious logic.

## Security

- Do NOT change access rules or remove security constraints without explanation.
- Changes to `ir.model.access` or record rules need PR explanation.

## POS

- Preserve checkout speed; avoid unnecessary UI friction; do not break barcode flow; consider offline compatibility.

## Inventory

- Do not break stock valuation or product variants; avoid modifying core stock moves unless necessary.

## Guiding principle

Build a clean retail POS first: **POS + inventory + customers** working well. Do not prematurely build rentals, service systems, or complex multi-location features.

When unsure: ask, propose options, avoid assumptions.
